# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 6: CODE CONVENTIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 6.1 TypeScript rules
- strict: true in tsconfig -- no exceptions, no @ts-ignore without explanation
- noImplicitAny: true
- strictNullChecks: true
- All props typed with interfaces (not type aliases) for components
- All API responses typed -- never use `any`
- Generated Supabase types from `supabase gen types typescript` -- never hand-write DB types
- Zod schemas for all form validation and all external API responses
- Generic return types: always `Promise<Result<T, AppError>>` for service functions
- No enums -- use `as const` objects with typeof for type extraction

## 6.2 Component conventions
- Functional components only -- no class components
- Component file exports: one default export (the component) + named exports for types
- Props interface named ComponentNameProps
- No inline styles -- all styles via StyleSheet.create() or theme constants
- No hardcoded colors -- always from constants/theme.ts
- No hardcoded strings -- always from i18n
- Error boundary wrapper on every screen component
- Loading state: skeleton screens, never ActivityIndicator spinners
- Empty state: dedicated EmptyState component, never null render

## 6.3 Service layer conventions
- All Supabase queries in /services/ -- never inline in components or hooks
- Service functions return typed results -- never throw, always return error objects
- Standard service return type:
  type ServiceResult<T> = { data: T; error: null } | { data: null; error: AppError }
- Always check RLS -- assume user can only access their own data
- Use Supabase pooled connection URL (not direct) for all client queries
- Mutations: always include optimistic update logic via TanStack Query

## 6.4 State management conventions
- TanStack Query: all server data -- workouts, diet, runs, social, AI responses
- Zustand: UI state + active session state (active workout, live run)
- No Redux, no Context API for global state
- Query keys: always from constants/queryKeys.ts factory -- never inline strings
- Invalidation: always invalidate related queries after mutations
- Stale time: 5 minutes for user data, 1 hour for library data (exercises, foods)
- Offline: useMutation with onMutate for optimistic updates + rollback on error

## 6.5 Async patterns
- Always async/await -- no .then() chains
- Always try/catch in service functions
- Never let errors bubble uncaught to the UI
- Network errors handled globally via TanStack Query onError
- Supabase realtime subscriptions cleaned up in useEffect return function

## 6.6 Naming conventions
- Files: PascalCase for components, camelCase for everything else
- Screens: NameScreen.tsx (e.g. HomeScreen.tsx, ActiveWorkoutScreen.tsx)
- Services: name.service.ts (e.g. workout.service.ts)
- Hooks: useFeatureName.ts (e.g. useWorkouts.ts)
- Stores: name.store.ts (e.g. auth.store.ts)
- Types: name.types.ts (e.g. workout.types.ts)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE for values, camelCase for objects
- Database columns: snake_case (matches PostgreSQL convention)
- TypeScript interfaces: PascalCase, no I prefix
- Zod schemas: camelCase with Schema suffix (e.g. loginSchema)

## 6.7 Git conventions
- Branch naming: feature/short-description, fix/issue-description, chore/task
- Commit format: type(scope): description (conventional commits)
  feat(workout): add rest timer with haptic feedback
  fix(diet): correct calorie calculation for custom serving sizes
  chore(deps): update expo-location to 17.0.1
- PR title must match conventional commit format
- No direct commits to main -- all changes via PR
- Squash merge PRs (clean linear history)


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 7: DESIGN SYSTEM (enforce in all generated UI code)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 7.1 Color tokens (from constants/theme.ts -- always import, never hardcode)
Background:
  BG_BASE:        '#0a0a0b'   // app background
  BG_SURFACE:     '#111114'   // card backgrounds
  BG_SURFACE_2:   '#18181d'   // input fields, inner cards
  BG_SURFACE_3:   '#1f1f26'   // hover states, inactive

Text:
  TEXT_PRIMARY:   '#f0eff4'   // main text
  TEXT_SECONDARY: '#8e8d9a'   // muted, descriptions
  TEXT_TERTIARY:  '#4e4d5a'   // hints, placeholders, labels

Accent (primary brand):
  ACCENT:         '#c8f53a'   // CTAs, active states, success, streaks
  ACCENT_DIM:     'rgba(200,245,58,0.12)'
  ACCENT_2:       '#a8e020'   // hover state of accent

Semantic:
  RED:            '#ff4d6a'   // errors, danger, high HR zone
  RED_DIM:        'rgba(255,77,106,0.12)'
  ORANGE:         '#ff9500'   // timers, warnings, calories
  ORANGE_DIM:     'rgba(255,149,0,0.12)'
  BLUE:           '#4d9fff'   // info, GPS, water intake
  BLUE_DIM:       'rgba(77,159,255,0.12)'
  TEAL:           '#2dd9b0'   // health, sleep, recovery
  TEAL_DIM:       'rgba(45,217,176,0.12)'
  PURPLE:         '#b87bff'   // AI, premium, yoga
  PURPLE_DIM:     'rgba(184,123,255,0.12)'

Border:
  BORDER:         'rgba(255,255,255,0.07)'   // default borders
  BORDER_2:       'rgba(255,255,255,0.12)'   // emphasis borders

## 7.2 Typography tokens
FONT_DISPLAY:   'Syne'          // headings, numbers, brand moments
FONT_BODY:      'DM Sans'       // all body text, labels, descriptions
FONT_MONO:      'JetBrains Mono' // all data: stats, metrics, code, times

Type scale:
  DISPLAY_XL:   { fontFamily: FONT_DISPLAY, fontSize: 72, fontWeight: '800', letterSpacing: -2 }
  DISPLAY_LG:   { fontFamily: FONT_DISPLAY, fontSize: 48, fontWeight: '800', letterSpacing: -1.5 }
  DISPLAY_MD:   { fontFamily: FONT_DISPLAY, fontSize: 32, fontWeight: '700', letterSpacing: -1 }
  DISPLAY_SM:   { fontFamily: FONT_DISPLAY, fontSize: 22, fontWeight: '700', letterSpacing: -0.5 }
  HEADING:      { fontFamily: FONT_DISPLAY, fontSize: 18, fontWeight: '700' }
  BODY_LG:      { fontFamily: FONT_BODY, fontSize: 16, fontWeight: '400', lineHeight: 26 }
  BODY_MD:      { fontFamily: FONT_BODY, fontSize: 14, fontWeight: '400', lineHeight: 22 }
  BODY_SM:      { fontFamily: FONT_BODY, fontSize: 12, fontWeight: '400', lineHeight: 18 }
  LABEL:        { fontFamily: FONT_BODY, fontSize: 13, fontWeight: '500' }
  CAPTION:      { fontFamily: FONT_BODY, fontSize: 11, fontWeight: '400', color: TEXT_SECONDARY }
  DATA_LG:      { fontFamily: FONT_MONO, fontSize: 24, fontWeight: '500' }
  DATA_MD:      { fontFamily: FONT_MONO, fontSize: 14, fontWeight: '400' }
  DATA_SM:      { fontFamily: FONT_MONO, fontSize: 11, fontWeight: '400' }
  EYEBROW:      { fontFamily: FONT_MONO, fontSize: 10, fontWeight: '500', letterSpacing: 0.1, textTransform: 'uppercase' }

## 7.3 Spacing (8pt grid -- always multiples of 4 or 8)
SPACE_1:   4
SPACE_2:   8
SPACE_3:   12
SPACE_4:   16
SPACE_5:   20    // standard horizontal screen padding
SPACE_6:   24
SPACE_8:   32
SPACE_10:  40
SPACE_12:  48

## 7.4 Border radius
RADIUS_SM:   10
RADIUS_MD:   16
RADIUS_LG:   22
RADIUS_XL:   32
RADIUS_FULL: 999  // pills, circular elements

## 7.5 Component sizing
Touch targets:    minimum 44px height (Apple HIG requirement)
Primary CTA:      56px height, full width, RADIUS_FULL, ACCENT background
Secondary button: 44px height, BORDER_2 border, transparent background
Icon buttons:     44x44px minimum, circular (RADIUS_FULL)
Bottom nav items: 64px height touch target
Input fields:     48px height, RADIUS_MD, BG_SURFACE_2 background
Cards:            RADIUS_LG, BG_SURFACE, BORDER border (0.5px or StyleSheet hairlineWidth)
Screen padding:   horizontal 20px always (SPACE_5)

## 7.6 UX enforcement rules (generated UI must follow these)
- No ActivityIndicator spinners -- skeleton screens only during loading
- Optimistic UI on all mutations -- update UI immediately, revert on error
- Primary action always in bottom 40% of screen (reachable with thumb)
- Empty states: always render EmptyState component, never return null
- Error states: always render inline error with retry action
- Offline indicator: subtle banner at top when no network, never block the UI
- All text in i18n -- never hardcode English strings in JSX
- Progress photos default to private -- never auto-share
- AI responses always stream (stream: true on Claude API) -- never wait for full response
- Haptic feedback on: button press (light), PR achievement (heavy), rest timer done (medium)


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 8: AI COACH INTEGRATION
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 8.1 Claude API configuration
Model:           claude-sonnet-4-5 (production), claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 (fast/cheap ops)
Max tokens:      1024 (chat responses), 2048 (weekly analysis)
Temperature:     0.7 (conversational), 0.3 (analysis and meal plans)
Stream:          true -- always stream responses to UI
Timeout:         30 seconds -- abort and show error after this

## 8.2 System prompt structure (always build this way)
You are Kai, a professional AI fitness and nutrition coach inside FitNepal.
You speak in the user's preferred language (${user.language}).
You are direct, evidence-based, and motivating without being toxic.

User profile:
  Name: ${user.display_name}
  Goal: ${user.goal}
  Fitness level: ${user.fitness_level}
  Age: ${calculateAge(user.date_of_birth)}
  Current weight: ${latestMetric.weight_kg}kg
  Target: ${user.goal_weight_kg}kg

Last 7 days summary:
  Workouts: ${workoutCount} of ${targetWorkouts} planned
  Avg daily calories: ${avgCalories} (target: ${tdee})
  Avg protein: ${avgProtein}g (target: ${proteinTarget}g)
  Avg sleep: ${avgSleep}h
  Total km run: ${totalKm}km
  Current streak: ${streak} days

Constraints:
  Never recommend calories below 1200 kcal/day.
  Never recommend more than 1kg/week weight loss.
  Always recommend consulting a doctor for injuries.
  Suggest Nepali foods when relevant (dal bhat, momo, chiura, gundruk, etc).

## 8.3 Caching strategy for AI responses
Key format:      ai:${userId}:${sha256(systemPrompt + userMessage)}
TTL:             86400 seconds (24 hours)
Skip cache when: user explicitly asks to refresh, weekly report generation
Cache on:        Upstash Redis via @upstash/redis SDK

## 8.4 Rate limiting
Free tier:       5 AI requests per day per user
Pro tier:        50 AI requests per day per user
Elite tier:      unlimited
Implementation:  Upstash Redis sliding window counter, key: ratelimit:ai:${userId}


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 9: NEPAL-SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 9.1 Localization
Default language:     Nepali (ne) -- set during onboarding, stored in users.language
Fallback language:    English (en)
i18n library:         react-i18next
Translation files:    /src/i18n/ne.json and en.json
Currency display:     NPR (Nepali Rupee) -- format: NPR 499 (no comma for thousands in NPR)
Date format:          DD/MM/YYYY (Nepal standard)
Time format:          12-hour with AM/PM
Timezone:             Asia/Kathmandu (UTC+5:45) -- note: not a standard offset
Week start:           Sunday

## 9.2 Nepali food database
Priority foods to include in seed data (with accurate nutrition per 100g):
  Dal bhat (with mixed sabzi and achar)
  Momos (buff, chicken, veg -- steamed and fried variants)
  Sel roti
  Chiura (beaten rice)
  Gundruk
  Aloo tama (potato and bamboo shoot curry)
  Chatamari
  Newari samay baji platter
  Yomari
  Thukpa (Tibetan noodle soup variant)
  Kwati (mixed bean soup)
  Saag (mustard greens)
  Dhindo

## 9.3 Payment flow (Nepal)
eSewa integration:
  Endpoint:   https://epay.esewa.com.np/api/epay/main/v2/form (production)
  Test:       https://rc-epay.esewa.com.np/api/epay/main/v2/form
  Flow:       POST form -> eSewa hosted page -> callback to /payment/esewa/callback
  Verify:     GET https://epay.esewa.com.np/api/epay/transaction/status/
  Secret:     ESEWA_SECRET env var -- HMAC-SHA256 signature required

Khalti integration:
  Endpoint:   https://khalti.com/api/v2/epayment/initiate/ (production)
  Flow:       POST initiate -> redirect to Khalti -> callback to /payment/khalti/callback
  Verify:     POST https://khalti.com/api/v2/epayment/lookup/
  Secret:     KHALTI_SECRET env var

## 9.4 GPS and mapping context
Kathmandu center coordinates:  27.7172, 85.3240
Pokhara center coordinates:    28.2096, 83.9856
Popular running routes to seed: Ratna Park loop, Tundikhel, Phewa Lake perimeter
Elevation data: important for Nepal (Kathmandu valley at 1400m, trekking routes)
Map provider: Google Maps API (react-native-maps default on Android)
              Apple Maps (react-native-maps default on iOS -- no API key needed)


